      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Discord default account startup priority",
        "body": "Fixes #77429\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Discord multi-account startup delay ordering previously followed the configured account id list directly, so a configured primary account such as `channels.discord.defaultAccount: \"tech\"` could be assigned a delayed startup slot when secondary account ids sorted before it.\r\n- Real environment tested: Isolated OpenClaw PR-head worktree at `/private/tmp/openclaw-pr89744-proof`, commit `8deff209b4f468f2a9e704adfc63ec18de367444`, on macOS. The proof used the production Discord gateway startup function in `extensions/discord/src/channel.ts` with my real local multi-account Discord config and Infisical-injected real Discord bot token environment. A temporary in-memory config overlay set `channels.discord.defaultAccount = \"tech\"`; no token values were written to disk or included below.\r\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ /Users/andy/.openclaw/workspace-tech/bin/infisical-env-run --paths /messaging -- \\\r\n    env PROOF_PR_HEAD=8deff209b4f468f2a9e704adfc63ec18de367444 \\\r\n    PROOF_ABORT_AFTER_MS=4500 \\\r\n    node --import tsx scripts/proof-discord-default-startup.ts tech\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Evidence after fix: Redacted live runtime log excerpt from the real Discord gateway startup path:\r\n\r\n```text\r\n[infisical-env] loaded 12 secrets from 1 paths\r\nt+   27ms proof PR head 8deff209b4f468f2a9e704adfc63ec18de367444 defaultAccount=tech\r\nt+   27ms proof gateway listAccountIds order=default,ecom,finance,tech,work\r\nt+   27ms proof pre-patch sorted slot for tech would be index=3\r\nt+   28ms proof [default] enabled=true tokenStatus=available tokenSource=config\r\nt+   28ms proof [ecom] enabled=true tokenStatus=available tokenSource=config\r\nt+   28ms proof [finance] enabled=true tokenStatus=available tokenSource=config\r\nt+   28ms proof [tech] enabled=true tokenStatus=available tokenSource=config\r\nt+   28ms proof [work] enabled=true tokenStatus=available tokenSource=config\r\nt+   28ms log:default:info [default] delaying provider startup 10s to reduce Discord startup rate limits\r\nt+   28ms log:ecom:info [ecom] delaying provider startup 20s to reduce Discord startup rate limits\r\nt+   28ms log:finance:info [finance] delaying provider startup 30s to reduce Discord startup rate limits\r\nt+   47ms log:tech:info [tech] starting provider\r\nt+ 3365ms log:work:info [work] delaying provider startup 40s to reduce Discord startup rate limits\r\nt+ 4256ms status:tech {\"accountId\":\"tech\",\"bot\":{\"id\":\"[REDACTED]\",\"username\":\"CTO\"},\"application\":{\"id\":\"[REDACTED]\",\"flags\":11051008,\"intents\":{\"presence\":\"limited\",\"guildMembers\":\"limited\",\"messageContent\":\"limited\"}}}\r\nt+ 4257ms log:tech:info [tech] Discord bot probe resolved @CTO\r\nt+ 5343ms runtime:log discord client initialized as [REDACTED]; awaiting gateway readiness\r\nt+ 6008ms status:tech {\"accountId\":\"tech\",\"connected\":true,\"lastConnectedAt\":\"[REDACTED]\",\"lastEventAt\":\"[REDACTED]\",\"lastDisconnect\":null,\"lastError\":null}\r\nt+ 7867ms proof aborting bounded proof run\r\nt+ 7869ms proof [default] startAccount returned\r\nt+ 7869ms proof [ecom] startAccount returned\r\nt+ 7869ms proof [finance] startAccount returned\r\nt+ 7869ms proof [work] startAccount returned\r\nt+ 7869ms status:tech {\"accountId\":\"tech\",\"connected\":false}\r\nt+ 7869ms proof [tech] startAccount returned\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Observed result after fix: The real Discord startup path saw the configured default account `tech` with available real token material. In the gateway's normal sorted account list, `tech` would have been index 3 and therefore delayed by about 30s before this patch. With the patch, `tech` entered provider startup at 47ms and reached Discord connected status; secondary accounts were assigned the 10s, 20s, 30s, and 40s staggered slots.\r\n- What was not tested: No Discord messages were sent. The proof intentionally aborted after the default account reached gateway readiness so secondary delayed accounts did not proceed to provider startup.\r\n\r\n## Supplemental validation\r\n\r\nFocused validation also run:\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ pnpm exec oxfmt --write extensions/discord/src/channel.ts extensions/discord/src/channel.test.ts\r\n$ pnpm test:extension discord extensions/discord/src/channel.test.ts\r\n$ env OPENCLAW_TSGO_HEAVY_CHECK_LOCK_HELD=1 node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test.tsbuildinfo\r\n$ git diff --check -- extensions/discord/src/channel.ts extensions/discord/src/channel.test.ts\r\n```\r\n\r\nEvidence from focused validation:\r\n\r\n```text\r\npnpm test:extension discord extensions/discord/src/channel.test.ts\r\nTest Files  160 passed (160)\r\nTests       1743 passed (1743)\r\n\r\nenv OPENCLAW_TSGO_HEAVY_CHECK_LOCK_HELD=1 node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test.tsbuildinfo\r\nexit code 0\r\n\r\ngit diff --check -- extensions/discord/src/channel.ts extensions/discord/src/channel.test.ts\r\nexit code 0\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Promotes the resolved Discord default account to the first startup slot only when it is enabled and configured for runtime startup.\r\n- Preserves existing secondary account stagger behavior after the promoted default account.\r\n- Does not change Discord usage UI, memory-core, Mattermost, or MCP code.\r\n",
